✨My favorite genre is black women living their BEST life and looking amazing while doing it! 🫶🏽 

Earlier this year I decided I would purposely recycle my outfits from previous years. Don’t get me wrong, I love buying new clothes but social media has changed the game and people often don’t repeat outfits that have been only been worn once or if they were photographed in the outfit and posted the pics on social media. So I have made an intentional effort to stay out the stores and reduce my online shopping so I can wear what I have in my closet. Maybe my recent life changes made me aware that I needed to cut back in some areas, but so far I have enjoyed finding creative ways to mix and match my pieces with new shoes and bags! 🥰

✨Happy September 1st! ✨I’m looking forward to a new season and new opportunities! 🌸 

Over the last week, I’ve been in a quiet zone as I reflect on what’s next. Recently, God has opened some new doors for me, but I also realized that others doors must be closed to achieve all that God has in store for me.

Happy 18th Birthday to my first born, @pstrib! 

18 years ago you came into this world after I danced to Michael Jackson down the hallway and at your Nana’s house hoping you would just come out, but you came a day after your due date and that’s how you’ve been living life ever since…doing YOU! 

Parker the challenges you faced as an infant, toddler, and young boy prepared you for this world that you must now enter and navigate as an adult. You have the foundation, so now you must do the work that God had destined for you when you were in my womb! I want you to always remember these 18 things because one day they will come across your mind and it’ll hit you, “my mommy told me that!” 

1. Always put God first! Pray everyday! 
2. Make sure you always tithe. Give and He’ll give it back to you! 
3. Always watch out for your sister! You’re her example and role model. 
4. Don’t be a dusty dude… I didn’t raise you to be one! Always be honest! 
5. Get up and work! Nothing good comes fast or free! You’ve gotta grind, PERIOD! 
6. Remember your name. There’s a rich history behind your name so as you move through life, remember your family is always watching and counting on you to protect the name and the brand. 
7. Show your emotions. It’s ok to talk and communicate! I’ve taught you how to advocate on your behalf. 
8. Don’t ever hit a woman. If things get heated, leave….and call me and your sister, lol. 
9. Keep your friends close, but watch your enemies closer. 
10. Boundaries- they should always be respected. 
11. Control your anger- don’t ever let someone else get the best of you.
12. Think with the head on the top of your body. Trust it. 💯 
13. Have fun. Life is meant to be lived. 
14. Love doesn’t hurt and isn’t toxic. 
15. Always respect your elders and call your older loved ones! There’s a lot of knowledge you can learn from them.
16. A wise person listens before making the same mistakes.
17. When things go left, go right. Read your Bible. 
18. Always remember you only have ONE momma! Always show love and respect for the one God gave you!

#tiffanystribling #thestribletsmommy #parkerman #18thbirthday #scorpioseason #adulting #myfirstborn

Goodbye 2023….Hello 2024! ✨

Wow, 2023 was an incredibly hard year. Life changed for me last year and would forever be different for me and my kids. Over the last year I endured heartache, sadness, grief, anger, and betrayal…. BUT joy comes in the morning because while Satan was trying to destroy me God was softening my heart and showing me grace, mercy, love, and forgiveness. 2023 wasn’t a crystal stair, but I am in a better place than I was  this time last year and for that I give God all the glory. 

My last two cents…. ladies don’t be afraid to embrace love after a divorce! No one really talks about the guilt you feel after a divorce but I promise as you go through the process and choose to live life for YOU the guilt starts to slowly subside and a new journey can begin!
